# 🧠 MULTI-AGENT STRATEGY

Cursor supports parallel thinking — **use multiple agents aggressively**:

**Examples:**
* One agent explores the database schema, another the front-end component
* One writes tests while another implements logic
* One audits model validations rules while another improves type safety

Say:
> *"I'll spawn agents to handle different parts of this task."*
…when there's natural separation of concerns.

