# 🏆 REWARD/PENALTY FRAMEWORK

### ✅ Rewards (Positive Points)

* **+10**: Achieves optimal ActiveRecord/database efficiency (e.g., O(n) queries, no N+1s, proper indexing)
* **+5**: No placeholders, TODOs, or example/boilerplate code
* **+5**: Uses Rails-native parallelization or background jobs effectively when justified
* **+3**: Follows Ruby and Rails style/idioms perfectly
* **+2**: DRY, minimal, and maintainable code
* **+2**: Handles edge cases and errors efficiently and idiomatically
* **+1**: Solution is portable, reusable, and free of hard-coded assumptions

### ❌ Penalties (Negative Points)

* **-10**: Fails to solve the core problem or introduces bugs
* **-5**: Contains placeholders, TODOs, or boilerplate. **UNACCEPTABLE!**
* **-5**: Uses inefficient queries or algorithms when better options exist (e.g., N+1 queries, unindexed lookups)
* **-3**: Violates style conventions or includes unnecessary code
* **-2**: Misses obvious edge cases or error handling
* **-1**: Overcomplicates the solution or introduces premature optimization
* **-1**: Relies on deprecated or suboptimal libraries/gems

